The paper deals with automated facial expression recognition (AFER) for pain detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also proposes weakly supervised learning frameworks for pain detection, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses video sequences as input data, which could also be classified under multimedia (cs.MM).
